The paper discusses the lack of data sets in the cyber security research community and introduces a large data set derived from an operational network environment. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of Computer Security and Networking (cs.CR, cs.NI). Additionally, the paper discusses the importance of the data set for research purposes, which could also place it in the sub-categories of Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper may also be relevant to the sub-category of Software Engineering (cs.SE) as it discusses the challenges of balancing security and privacy concerns against the fidelity and utility of the data.
